<subSubSection id="539BA56C7DCB6DAEFC9FE2C49CFB3DD4" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="92F2FE2FCF36E1CC63F5A21B81E719CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E573BDD5761AD8BFF7C6049B72FE34DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: Belogradchik, 28.09.2009, 1 w., leg. P. Mitov; East Rhodopes, Kremen vill., 21.07.2009, 1 w., leg. ALG; Thracian Plane, Brestovitsa vill., 07.04.2012, sifting, 1 w., leg. R. Bekchiev. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="9C11841C4E9CCDFC1C4BB8CF70F61123" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C4F0BA321E7052E0852064669A1A1A6F" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="AF8F3B748EF4527EDD929FC6DB1C3D87" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A35B866A78F0B852728583CEB332603A" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName id="2DBA1EDC43520B5A1D5F067641D94B98" baseAuthorityName="Roger" baseAuthorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Proceratium" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Proceratium melinum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melinum">
<emphasis id="233897F36210DA1825EFD8DFA2139C89" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Proceratium melinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rarely collected due to its subterranean lifestyle and small colonies, although it is widespread in the Palaearctic. It is known in Bulgaria in a small number of localities (Dobrudzha, Thracian Lowland (Svilengrad), Struma Valley (Petrich, Sandanski) and Burgas) (
<bibRefCitation id="6F2238F98AB7825AD6BEF2BC792EC2D6" author="Forel, A." journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="305 - 318" refId="B7727072" refString="Forel, A., 1892. Die Ameisenfauna Bulgariens. (Nebst biologischen Beobachtungen). Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 42: 305 - 318" title="Die Ameisenfauna Bulgariens. (Nebst biologischen Beobachtungen)" volume="42" year="1892">Forel 1892</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F2AC0139F31589EE70D6AB47C05CB3CC" author="Atanassov, N." journalOrPublisher="Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7725616" refString="Atanassov, N., Dlussky, G. M., 1992. Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae. Bulgarian Academy of Sciences, Sofia" title="Fauna Bulgarica. 22. Hymenoptera, Formicidae" year="1992">Atanassov and Dlussky 1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="926EE73C610395F0AF038E55488506CE" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 124" refId="B7725831" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Antonova, V., Radchenko, A. G., Atanasova, M., 2010. Catalogue of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Bulgaria. ZooKeys 62: 1 - 124" title="Catalogue of the ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Bulgaria" volume="62" year="2010">Lapeva-Gjonova et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
